{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to investigate a Kubernetes v1.9.1 bug related to watch cache DELETE event handling. The local source files are NOT at /workspace - you MUST use Sourcegraph MCP tools to access the code.\n\nPlease search for and read the following files using Sourcegraph tools:\n\n1. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` - specifically the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function\n2. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` - specifically the `prepareObjs` and `decodeObj` functions\n3. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/watcher.go` - specifically DELETE event handling\n4. `pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go` - if it exists\n5. Client-go reflector code that tracks resourceVersion from watch events\n\nThe bug is: When the watch cache converts a MODIFY event to a DELETE event (because the object no longer matches the namespace filter), it sends the PrevObject with the old resourceVersion instead of the event's resourceVersion.\n\nThe fix should be similar to etcd3/watcher.go which calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to update the resourceVersion.\n\nUse Sourcegraph MCP tools to:\n1. Search for \"sendWatchCacheEvent\" \n2. Search for \"PrevObject\" near \"Deleted\"\n3. Read the full content of cacher.go around the sendWatchCacheEvent function\n4. Read etcd3/watcher.go around prepareObjs function\n\nReturn the exact code with file paths and line numbers."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"07ecb4e7-3f74-46c2-a0a0-49e784b5c3e1","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:47:51.579Z"}
