{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E2iV1m6MeNWMuF9MP99aQF","type":"tool_result","content":"# Resource Version Tracking from Watch Events\n\nThe code that tracks resourceVersion from watch events is found in the `watchHandler` method:\n\n**Lines 287-289:** Extract the resource version from the watch event object:\n```go\nmeta, err := meta.Accessor(event.Object)\nif err != nil {\n\tutilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"%s: unable to understand watch event %#v\", r.name, event))\n```\n\n**Line 292:** Retrieve the resourceVersion value:\n```go\nnewResourceVersion := meta.GetResourceVersion()\n```\n\n**Line 312:** Update the resourceVersion pointer with the new value obtained from the watch event:\n```go\n*resourceVersion = newResourceVersion\n```\n\n**Line 313:** Additionally persist this version:\n```go\nr.setLastSyncResourceVersion(newResourceVersion)\n```\n\nThe pattern shows that for each watch event (Added, Modified, or Deleted), the code extracts metadata from the event object, obtains its resourceVersion via `GetResourceVersion()`, and then updates both the local pointer parameter and the reflector's internal tracking field."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"40614e96-a59d-4a2a-8d39-46f267f5a92d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:48:29.325Z"}
