{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J6RaVKv1xVxvTHQiVkkEk9","type":"tool_result","content":"# Lines 325-360: Watch Event Handling\n\nHere are the requested lines with line numbers:\n\n```\n325    case watch.Deleted:\n326        // TODO: Will any consumers need access to the \"last known\n327        // state\", which is passed in event.Object? If so, may need\n328        // to change this.\n329        err := r.store.Delete(event.Object)\n330        if err != nil {\n331            utilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"%s: unable to delete watch event object (%#v) from store: %v\", r.name, event.Object, err))\n332        }\n333    default:\n334        utilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"%s: unable to understand watch event %#v\", r.name, event))\n335    }\n336    *resourceVersion = newResourceVersion\n337    *r.setLastSyncResourceVersion(newResourceVersion)\n338    eventCount++\n339    }\n340}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** After handling all event types (Added, Modified, or Deleted), the code updates the resource version at line 336 with `*resourceVersion = newResourceVersion`, then synchronizes the internal resource version tracker at line 337. This ensures the reflector maintains current state information following each watch event regardless of operation type."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"bbf04d75-4604-47e0-9252-ce3118a12d08","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:48:46.351Z"}
