{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HSeuaj27hmJKpsy5bdrGHK","type":"tool_result","content":"# DELETE Event Handling Code\n\n## sendDelete Method (Lines 336-365)\n\nThe primary DELETE event handling occurs in the `sendDelete` function:\n\n**Lines 336-341:** Function signature and nil check\n```\nfunc (w *etcdWatcher) sendDelete(res *etcd.Response) {\n\tif res.PrevNode == nil {\n\t\tutilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected nil prev node: %#v\", res))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n```\n\n**Lines 342-343:** Include filter check\n```\n\tif w.include != nil && !w.include(res.PrevNode.Key) {\n\t\treturn\n```\n\n**Lines 344-351:** Previous node handling and index update\n```\n\tnode := *res.PrevNode\n\tif res.Node != nil {\n\t\t// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n\t\t// which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right\n\t\t// index.\n\t\tnode.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex\n\t}\n```\n\n**Lines 357-361:** Event emission with Deleted type\n```\n\tif !w.filter(obj) {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tw.emit(watch.Event{\n\t\tType:   watch.Deleted,\n\t\tObject: obj,\n\t})\n```\n\n## sendResult Router (Lines 368-381)\n\nThe router dispatches DELETE operations:\n\n```\ncase EtcdDelete, EtcdExpire, EtcdCAD:\n\tw.sendDelete(res)\n```\n\n**Key detail:** The DELETE handler reconstructs the object from the previous node state (`res.PrevNode`) to emit the deleted object in the watch event."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"0fcba621-e771-4777-a337-d11d6a65c5e6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:48:57.513Z"}
