{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EteCVNuUjBZXeo8ojVXvqP","type":"tool_result","content":"# watchCacheEvent Struct Definition and ResourceVersion Usage\n\n## Struct Definition (Lines 44-55)\n\n```go\ntype watchCacheEvent struct {\n\tType                 watch.EventType\n\tObject               runtime.Object\n\tObjLabels            labels.Set\n\tObjFields            fields.Set\n\tObjUninitialized     bool\n\tPrevObject           runtime.Object\n\tPrevObjLabels        labels.Set\n\tPrevObjFields        fields.Set\n\tPrevObjUninitialized bool\n\tKey                  string\n\tResourceVersion      uint64\n}\n```\n\n## Event Construction Locations\n\n**Primary construction (Lines 232-246):** In the `processEvent` method, a new event is built with current and previous object attributes:\n\n```go\nwatchCacheEvent := &watchCacheEvent{\n\tType:                 event.Type,\n\tObject:               event.Object,\n\tObjLabels:            objLabels,\n\tObjFields:            objFields,\n\tObjUninitialized:     objUninitialized,\n\tPrevObject:           prevObject,\n\tPrevObjLabels:        prevObjLabels,\n\tPrevObjFields:        prevObjFields,\n\tPrevObjUninitialized: prevObjUninitialized,\n\tKey:                  key,\n\tResourceVersion:      resourceVersion,\n}\n```\n\n**Secondary construction (Lines 356-366):** In `GetAllEventsSinceThreadUnsafe`, events are synthesized when `resourceVersion == 0`:\n\n```go\nresult[i] = &watchCacheEvent{\n\tType:             watch.Added,\n\tObject:           elem.Object,\n\tObjLabels:        objLabels,\n\tObjFields:        objFields,\n\tObjUninitialized: objUninitialized,\n\tKey:              elem.Key,\n\tResourceVersion:  w.resourceVersion,\n}\n```\n\nThe `ResourceVersion` field is a `uint64` representing the object's version state."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"8cdff6be-a0b4-44c2-87d2-2bb86dbaf8d7","timestamp":"2026-