{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kc4heytELkPjZJGB3E7U2u","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed to give a complete analysis. Here is the full investigation report:\n\n---\n\n## Bug Investigation: Watch Cache DELETE Event ResourceVersion Bug in Kubernetes v1.9.1\n\n### 1. The Buggy Code\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\nThe `sendWatchCacheEvent` function (lines 641-684):\n\n```go\n// NOTE: sendWatchCacheEvent is assumed to not modify <event> !!!\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) sendWatchCacheEvent(event *watchCacheEvent) {     // line 641\n    curObjPasses := event.Type != watch.Deleted && c.filter(event.Key, event.ObjLabels, event.ObjFields, event.ObjUninitialized)\n    oldObjPasses := false\n    if event.PrevObject != nil {\n        oldObjPasses = c.filter(event.Key, event.PrevObjLabels, event.PrevObjFields, event.PrevObjUninitialized)\n    }\n    if !curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses {\n        // Watcher is not interested in that object.\n        return\n    }\n\n    var watchEvent watch.Event\n    switch {\n    case curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Added, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Modified, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:                                                        // line 658\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}  // line 659 ← BUG\n    }\n    ...\n    select {\n    case c.result <- watchEvent:\n    case <-c.done:\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**The bug is on line 659.** When a MODIFY event is converted to a synthesized DELETE event (because the new object no longer passes the namespace/label filter, but the old one did), the code emits `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` as the deleted object. The `PrevObject` carries the **old resourceVersion** — the version before the modification — not the event's current `ResourceVersion` (`event.ResourceVersion`, the version of the modifying transaction).\n\n---\n\n### 2. The watchCacheEvent Struct\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` (lines 44-55):\n\n```go\ntype watchCacheEvent struct {\n    Type                 watch.EventType\n    Object               runtime.Object\n    ObjLabels            labels.Set\n    ObjFields            fields.Set\n    ObjUninitialized     bool\n    PrevObject           runtime.Object      // ← carries stale resourceVersion\n    PrevObjLabels        labels.Set\n    PrevObjFields        fields.Set\n    PrevObjUninitialized bool\n    Key                  string\n    ResourceVersion      uint64              // ← this is the correct, current version\n}\n```\n\n`event.ResourceVersion` is set correctly to the etcd revision of the current event. `event.PrevObject` retains the object as it was before the change, with its old resourceVersion embedded in object metadata.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How the Reflector Is Affected\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go`\n\nThe `watchHandler` method (lines 281-339):\n\n```go\nmeta, err := meta.Accessor(event.Object)      // line 312\n...\nnewResourceVersion := meta.GetResourceVersion() // line 317\nswitch event.Type {\n...\ncase watch.Deleted:                            // line 325\n    err := r.store.Delete(event.Object)\n    ...\n}\n*resourceVersion = newResourceVersion          // line 336\nr.setLastSyncResourceVersion(newResourceVersion) // line 337\n```\n\nThe reflector extracts `resourceVersion` directly from `event.Object` via `meta.GetResourceVersion()`. When the watch cache sends a synthesized DELETE with `PrevObject` (which has the **old** resourceVersion), the reflector records the old resourceVersion as the latest seen. On the next re-list or re-watch, it will use this stale resourceVersion, potentially causing it to re-receive events it already processed or miss the gap.\n\n---\n\n### 4. The Reference Fix in etcd3/watcher.go\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n\nThe `prepareObjs` function (lines 250-278) and `decodeObj` (lines 280-299):\n\n```go\nfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n    ...\n    // For deletion, old object is decoded with e.rev (the current etcd revision)\n    if len(e.prevValue) > 0 && (e.isDeleted || !wc.acceptAll()) {\n        data, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.prevValue, ...)\n        ...\n        // Note: sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at which it gets deleted.\n        oldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev) // line 272\n    }\n    ...\n}\n\nfunc decodeObj(codec runtime.Codec, versioner storage.Versioner, data []byte, rev int64) (_ runtime.Object, err error) {\n    obj, err := runtime.Decode(codec, []byte(data))\n    ...\n    // ensure resource version is set on the object we load from etcd\n    if err := versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)); err != nil {  // line 295 ← THE FIX PATTERN\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", rev, obj, err)\n    }\n    return obj, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe etcd3 watcher explicitly calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to **stamp the current etcd revision** (`e.rev`) onto the previous object before emitting it in a DELETE event. This ensures the emitted object carries the correct, current resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n### 5. The Fix\n\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function needs to update the resourceVersion of the `PrevObject` deep copy before emitting the DELETE event:\n\n**Buggy line 659:**\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\n**Fixed version:**\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    obj := event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()\n    if err := c.versioner.UpdateObject(obj, event.ResourceVersion); err != nil {\n        utilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", event.ResourceVersion, obj, err))\n    }\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: obj}\n```\n\nThis mirrors exactly what `etcd3/watcher.go` does in `decodeObj` at line 295: calling `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to stamp the current event's revision onto the object before it is emitted, so the reflector records the correct, current resourceVersion from the DELETE event.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Location | File | Lines | Issue |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Bug** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | 658-659 | Emits `PrevObject` with stale resourceVersion for synthesized DELETE |\n| **Struct** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | 44-55 | `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` has correct version; `PrevObject` has stale |\n| **Reflector impact** | `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go` | 317, 336 | Reads resourceVersion from `event.Object` metadata; gets wrong value |\n| **Fix pattern** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` | 272, 295 | `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` stamps current revision onto prev object |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a07a794b5db885a52 (use SendMessage with to: 'a07a794b5db885a52' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 25629\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 117949</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"ed1ad81e-70a2-407d-9eed-9581f1eb6051","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:49:49.528Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to investigate a Kubernetes v1.9.1 bug related to watch cache DELETE event handling. The local source files are NOT at /workspace - you MUST use Sourcegraph MCP tools to access the code.\n\nPlease search for and read the following files using Sourcegraph tools:\n\n1. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` - specifically the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function\n2. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` - specifically the `prepareObjs` and `decodeObj` functions\n3. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/watcher.go` - specifically DELETE event handling\n4. `pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go` - if it exists\n5. Client-go reflector code that tracks resourceVersion from watch events\n\nThe bug is: When the watch cache converts a MODIFY event to a DELETE event (because the object no longer matches the namespace filter), it sends the PrevObject with the old resourceVersion instead of the event's resourceVersion.\n\nThe fix should be similar to etcd3/watcher.go which calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to update the resourceVersion.\n\nUse Sourcegraph MCP tools to:\n1. Search for \"sendWatchCacheEvent\" \n2. Search for \"PrevObject\" near \"Deleted\"\n3. Read the full content of cacher.go around the sendWatchCacheEvent function\n4. Read etcd3/watcher.go around prepareObjs function\n\nReturn the exact code with file paths and line numbers.","agentId":"a07a794b5db885a52","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed to give a complete analysis. Here is the full investigation report:\n\n---\n\n## Bug Investigation: Watch Cache DELETE Event ResourceVersion Bug in Kubernetes v1.9.1\n\n### 1. The Buggy Code\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\nThe `sendWatchCacheEvent` function (lines 641-684):\n\n```go\n// NOTE: sendWatchCacheEvent is assumed to not modify <event> !!!\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) sendWatchCacheEvent(event *watchCacheEvent) {     // line 641\n    curObjPasses := event.Type != watch.Deleted && c.filter(event.Key, event.ObjLabels, event.ObjFields, event.ObjUninitialized)\n    oldObjPasses := false\n    if event.PrevObject != nil {\n        oldObjPasses = c.filter(event.Key, event.PrevObjLabels, event.PrevObjFields, event.PrevObjUninitialized)\n    }\n    if !curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses {\n        // Watcher is not interested in that object.\n        return\n    }\n\n    var watchEvent watch.Event\n    switch {\n    case curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Added, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Modified, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:                                                        // line 658\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}  // line 659 ← BUG\n    }\n    ...\n    select {\n    case c.result <- watchEvent:\n    case <-c.done:\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**The bug is on line 659.** When a MODIFY event is converted to a synthesized DELETE event (because the new object no longer passes the namespace/label filter, but the old one did), the code emits `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` as the deleted object. The `PrevObject` carries the **old resourceVersion** — the version before the modification — not the event's current `ResourceVersion` (`event.ResourceVersion`, the version of the modifying transaction).\n\n---\n\n### 2. The watchCacheEvent Struct\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` (lines 44-55):\n\n```go\ntype watchCacheEvent struct {\n    Type                 watch.EventType\n    Object               runtime.Object\n    ObjLabels            labels.Set\n    ObjFields            fields.Set\n    ObjUninitialized     bool\n    PrevObject           runtime.Object      // ← carries stale resourceVersion\n    PrevObjLabels        labels.Set\n    PrevObjFields        fields.Set\n    PrevObjUninitialized bool\n    Key                  string\n    ResourceVersion      uint64              // ← this is the correct, current version\n}\n```\n\n`event.ResourceVersion` is set correctly to the etcd revision of the current event. `event.PrevObject` retains the object as it was before the change, with its old resourceVersion embedded in object metadata.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How the Reflector Is Affected\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go`\n\nThe `watchHandler` method (lines 281-339):\n\n```go\nmeta, err := meta.Accessor(event.Object)      // line 312\n...\nnewResourceVersion := meta.GetResourceVersion() // line 317\nswitch event.Type {\n...\ncase watch.Deleted:                            // line 325\n    err := r.store.Delete(event.Object)\n    ...\n}\n*resourceVersion = newResourceVersion          // line 336\nr.setLastSyncResourceVersion(newResourceVersion) // line 337\n```\n\nThe reflector extracts `resourceVersion` directly from `event.Object` via `meta.GetResourceVersion()`. When the watch cache sends a synthesized DELETE with `PrevObject` (which has the **old** resourceVersion), the reflector records the old resourceVersion as the latest seen. On the next re-list or re-watch, it will use this stale resourceVersion, potentially causing it to re-receive events it already processed or miss the gap.\n\n---\n\n### 4. The Reference Fix in etcd3/watcher.go\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n\nThe `prepareObjs` function (lines 250-278) and `decodeObj` (lines 280-299):\n\n```go\nfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n    ...\n    // For deletion, old object is decoded with e.rev (the current etcd revision)\n    if len(e.prevValue) > 0 && (e.isDeleted || !wc.acceptAll()) {\n        data, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.prevValue, ...)\n        ...\n        // Note: sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at which it gets deleted.\n        oldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev) // line 272\n    }\n    ...\n}\n\nfunc decodeObj(codec runtime.Codec, versioner storage.Versioner, data []byte, rev int64) (_ runtime.Object, err error) {\n    obj, err := runtime.Decode(codec, []byte(data))\n    ...\n    // ensure resource version is set on the object we load from etcd\n    if err := versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)); err != nil {  // line 295 ← THE FIX PATTERN\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", rev, obj, err)\n    }\n    return obj, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe etcd3 watcher explicitly calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to **stamp the current etcd revision** (`e.rev`) onto the previous object before emitting it in a DELETE event. This ensures the emitted object carries the correct, current resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n### 5. The Fix\n\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`, the `sendWatchCacheEvent` function needs to update the resourceVersion of the `PrevObject` deep copy before emitting the DELETE event:\n\n**Buggy line 659:**\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\n**Fixed version:**\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    obj := event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()\n    if err := c.versioner.UpdateObject(obj, event.ResourceVersion); err != nil {\n        utilruntime.HandleError(fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", event.ResourceVersion, obj, err))\n    }\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: obj}\n```\n\nThis mirrors exactly what `etcd3/watcher.go` does in `decodeObj` at line 295: calling `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to stamp the current event's revision onto the object before it is emitted, so the reflector records the correct, current resourceVersion from the DELETE event.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Location | File | Lines | Issue |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Bug** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | 658-659 | Emits `PrevObject` with stale resourceVersion for synthesized DELETE |\n| **Struct** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | 44-55 | `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` has correct version; `PrevObject` has stale |\n| **Reflector impact** | `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go` | 317, 336 | Reads resourceVersion from `event.Object` metadata; gets wrong value |\n| **Fix pattern** | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` | 272, 295 | `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` stamps current revision onto prev object |"}],"totalDurationMs":117949,"totalTokens":25629,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":453,"cache_read_input_tokens":22980,"output_tokens":2195,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":453},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
