{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PieAYmmc3zRNkQAd6zcWm8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see that in `watch_cache.go`, the `watchCacheEvent` is created with `PrevObject: prevObject` and `ResourceVersion: resourceVersion`. The `prevObject` has the OLD resourceVersion embedded in it (from when it was stored). The `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` is set to the current event's resourceVersion.\n\nBut in `cacher.go:893`, when a synthesized DELETE event is sent, it uses `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` which retains the old resourceVersion from the previous object's metadata. It does NOT call `versioner.UpdateObject()` to stamp the current event's resourceVersion onto the PrevObject.\n \nSo this is the root cause. Now I need to trace back through `processEvent` to understand where the `prevObject` originates and confirm this is where the mismatch happens.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1971,"cache_read_input_tokens":28056,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1971},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9acb4ca3-911a-4067-a3ba-399174a3a531","uuid":"f3039b1d-c5dc-488d-8ca1-b2fedd240f81"}
