a (reflector.go:394,418)\",\n    \"Step 2: Watch request reaches API server Cacher.Watch() which creates a cacheWatcher fed from the watchCache event stream via sendWatchCacheEvent\",\n    \"Step 3: An object in the watched namespace is modified (e.g., moved to another namespace or labels changed to no longer match filter); etcd emits a MODIFY event\",\n    \"Step 4: watch_cache.go:processEvent receives the MODIFY event, fetches PrevObject from its in-memory store (the old object with its old resourceVersion), and creates a watchCacheEvent with PrevObject=<old object with stale RV> and ResourceVersion=<current event revision>\",\n    \"Step 5: sendWatchCacheEvent (cacher.go:875) evaluates the filter: new object fails namespace filter (curObjPasses=false), old object passes (oldObjPasses=true); the case !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses fires\",\n    \"Step 6: BUG — cacher.go:893 emits watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()} where PrevObject carries the stale resourceVersion from before the MODIFY event, NOT the current event's ResourceVersion\",\n    \"Step 7: Reflector's watchHandler receives DELETE event, calls meta.GetResourceVersion() on the event object, gets the stale old resourceVersion, and stores it via setLastSyncResourceVersion\",\n    \"Step 8: Watch connection drops (network issue, server restart, timeout); Reflector restarts watch using the stale resourceVersion\",\n    \"Step 9: API server only returns events newer than the provided resourceVersion; all events between the stale version and actual current version are permanently missed\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"A namespace-scoped watch is established via the API server watch cache (not direct etcd)\",\n    \"An object currently in the watched namespace is modified so it moves to a different namespace, OR its labels/fields change so it no longer matches the watch filter\",\n    \"The watch cache converts the MODIFY event into a synthesized DELETE event (